On a sunny, California Spring morning in 1995, we tried to come up with something completely unique. We decided to crush fresh with Arbequina, Arbosana and other prominent Californian olive varietals and thus managed to create a new, fresh twist on California olive oil. Our success with artisan olive oils soon led us to the crafting of wholly unique vinegars using locally-sourced wine and traditional fermentation methods. Our premium vinegars and olive oils give chefs and home cooks endless options to bring the fresh flavors of California to the table.

On a sunny, California day in 1995, O's founder did something totally original. He crushed fresh citrus with Arbequina olives and created a new twist on California olive oil. Our success with artisan olive oils soon led us to the crafting of wholly unique vinegars using locally-sourced wine and traditional fermentation methods. Our premium vinegars and olive oils give chefs and home cooks endless options to bring the fresh flavors of California to the table.

Our olive varietals are crushed hours after being harvested. This makes our olive oil the freshest and full of beneficial polyphenols and antioxidant richness. It's more work and expense , but totally worth it! The clean and fresh flavors are authentic and unmatched by other products.
